Bootstrap: docker
From: bioconductor/bioconductor_docker:RELEASE_3_20

%labels
    Author nf-core/riboseq
    Description RiboseQC container with PATCHED ORFquant 1.3.2 (Bioc 3.20 compat: disjointExons→exonicParts + txdbmaker + Position/combine/IRanges fixes)

%setup
    ROOTFS="${SINGULARITY_ROOTFS:-${APPTAINER_ROOTFS}}"
    mkdir -p "${ROOTFS}/etc"
    rm -f "${ROOTFS}/etc/resolv.conf"
    : > "${ROOTFS}/etc/resolv.conf"
    
    # Copy patched ORFquant source into the container
    mkdir -p "${ROOTFS}/opt/orfquant_patched"

%files
    # Copy the patched ORFquant 1.1 source directory into the container
    patched_packages/ORFquant-1.1 /opt/orfquant_patched/ORFquant-1.1

%post
    # Install RiboseQC (not in base Bioconductor Docker image)
    R --vanilla -q -e "if (!requireNamespace('remotes', quietly=TRUE)) install.packages('remotes', repos='https://cloud.r-project.org'); remotes::install_github('lcalviell/Ribo-seQC', upgrade='never', quiet=TRUE)"

    # Install patched ORFquant (dev branch) from local source
    # Patches applied:
    # 1. Bioc 3.20: disjointExons → exonicParts (2 calls in orfquant.R, lines ~1791, ~5133)
    #    - disjointExons was removed from GenomicFeatures in Bioc 3.20
    #    - exonicParts(..., linked.to.single.gene.only=FALSE) is the replacement
    # 2. NAMESPACE: Import order fixed - BiocGenerics imported LAST
    #    to ensure Position and combine don't get overridden by ggplot2/gridExtra
    # 3. orfquant.R: IRanges empty data protection added at lines 160 and 973
    #    to prevent "at least two out of start/end/width must be supplied" errors
    # 4. orfquant.R (line ~3105): P_sites_all empty data filter added
    #    to handle filtered BAMs (MT removed) with missing P-site data for some read lengths
    
    cat > /tmp/install_orfquant.R <<'RSCRIPT'
pkg_dir <- "/opt/orfquant_patched/ORFquant-1.1"

if (!dir.exists(pkg_dir)) {
    stop("Patched ORFquant source not found at: ", pkg_dir)
}

message("Installing patched ORFquant 1.1 from: ", pkg_dir)
cmd <- sprintf("R CMD INSTALL %s", shQuote(pkg_dir))
message(cmd)
status <- system(cmd)
if (status != 0) stop("R CMD INSTALL failed with status ", status)

# Verify no Position conflict warning
message("\n=== Verifying ORFquant installation ===")
library(ORFquant)
message("ORFquant version: ", packageVersion("ORFquant"))
message("Installation successful - no Position/combine conflict warnings should appear above!")
RSCRIPT

    # Install txdbmaker for Bioc 3.20+ compatibility
    # (needed by GenomicFeatures functions that were migrated to txdbmaker)
    R --vanilla -q -e "if (!requireNamespace('BiocManager', quietly=TRUE)) install.packages('BiocManager', repos='https://cloud.r-project.org'); BiocManager::install('txdbmaker', update=FALSE, ask=FALSE)"

    R --vanilla -q -f /tmp/install_orfquant.R

    # Ensure optparse is available for ORFquant classification helpers
    R --vanilla -q -e "if (!requireNamespace('optparse', quietly=TRUE)) install.packages('optparse', repos='https://cloud.r-project.org')"

%runscript
    exec "$@"

%help
    This container includes RiboseQC and PATCHED ORFquant 1.3.1 for Ribo-seq analysis.
    
    VERSION 1.3.0 PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATIONS:
    - DPSS caching: 3-34x speedup in spectral analysis
    - Vectorized calc_orf_pval: batch P-site extraction, vapply statistics
    - Optimized select_txs: vapply matrix construction
    - Early filtering: skip non-qualifying ORFs before expensive computations
    - Memory pre-allocation: reduced dynamic vector growth overhead
    
    PATCH DETAILS:
    - Bioc 3.20: disjointExons → exonicParts (2 locations in orfquant.R)
    - Bioc 3.20: txdbmaker pre-installed (GenomicFeatures functions migrated)
    - ORFquant NAMESPACE modified to import BiocGenerics LAST
    - Ensures BiocGenerics::Position and BiocGenerics::combine are not overridden
    - IRanges edge case protection added to prevent errors on empty data (2 locations)
    - P_sites_all validation filter for GRangesList with empty/invalid elements
    - Fixes "attempt to apply non-function" error in parallel ORFquant runs
    - Fixes "at least two out of start/end/width must be supplied" IRanges error
    - Handles filtered BAMs (MT removed) that may have missing P-sites for some read lengths
    
    Build:
        apptainer build --fakeroot -F orfquant_patched.sif containers/Singularity.orfquant.patched.def

    Use in nf-core/riboseq:
        nextflow run main.nf -profile test_local_singularity \
          --orfquant_container /abs/path/orfquant_patched.sif

    Usage:
        apptainer exec orfquant_patched.sif Rscript your_script.R
